  <thing id="cMPSGGCros" name="Cross-Training" description="A prize fighter is always pushing his physical conditioning, working to improve weaknesses as much as enhance his advantages. At 5th level, this constant undertaking grants the prize fighter a +1 inherent bonus to the lowest of his Strength, Dexterity, or Constitution score.\n\nWhen determining which score is lowest, only the actual score and other inherent bonuses are considered (no magic effects, even long-term magic benefits, apply).\n\nAt 9th, 14th, and 17th level, the prize fighter gains an additional +1 inherent bonus, applied to whatever ability score is lowest at the time this benefit is gained. If this would result in the prize fighter having two +1 inherent bonuses to the same ability score or a +1 and a +2, or a +1 and a +3, instead the higher inherent bonus is increased by 1." compset="ClSpecial">
